headline: Navient Q3 Earnings Beat on NII Growth & Lower Expenses, Provisions Up
summary: NAVI's Q3 earnings top estimates, fueled by higher net interest income and sharp cost cuts despite rising provisions.

headline: Capital One, Capital One Foundation, and Lever for Change Announce $25M Open Call to Expand Pathways to Homeownership
summary: CHICAGO, October 29, 2025--Today, Capital One, the Capital One Foundation, and Lever for Change announced the launch of Scaling Pathways to Homeownership, a $25 million Open Call designed to identify and support bold solutions that expand access to affordable homeownership in the United States. headline: How Investors Are Reacting To Capital One Financial (COF) Dividend Hike and $16 Billion Buyback Announcement
summary: In October 2025, Capital One Financial announced plans to raise its quarterly dividend from US$0.60 to US$0.80 per share, authorized a US$16 billion share repurchase program, and reported third-quarter earnings and net interest income that significantly surpassed prior-year results. Alongside these financial announcements, the company also disclosed higher net charge-offs, reflecting shifts in credit quality even as it executed bold shareholder return initiatives.
